HEADWORD: Unbuckle
<hw>Un*buc"kle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>buckle</ets>.]</ety> <def>To loose the buckles of;
to unfasten; <as>as, to <ex>unbuckle</ex> a shoe</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Unbuckle</xex> anon thy purse.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

